node.text: Last night was a true #Sliving experience. 🔥 I had such a fun time celebrating the premiere of #CookingWithParis with my friends and family.🥳👩🏼‍🍳⏲ I’m so thankful for everyone who helped turn a YouTube video into a @Netflix series. 🥰 I can’t wait to hear what you all think of my #ThatsHot cookbook and what recipes were your favorite! 🥣🍤🌮🍝🥗🥓🍳🍞

node.text: I will always support and love Britney. She is so kind and sweet, and she deserves her freedom. I’ve been saying #FreeBritney for a long time, and I will keep saying it until she is free. ❤️ We all need to use our voices to protect victims of abuse. She is so incredibly brave and an inspiration for speaking her truth. I know personally how hard it is to come forward to tell your story, and so I hope Britney knows that she is so loved and supported by the world right now. ❤️👑 #FreeBritney

node.text: On this week’s #SLIVING Self-Care, here are my tips for a good night’s sleep. 🛌😴 I learned from my friends at @GetR3set that getting a good night’s sleep reduces the production of stress hormones in the body. Good sleep is also linked to a strong immune system and better moods throughout the day. ✨💓✨ Learn more at ParisReset.com 💕 #SlivingSelfCare #Wellness

node.text: I am so proud of this film and all of the ways it has led me on my own journey of growth and healing. 🎥 I’m so honored to be showing my #ThisIsParis documentary directed by @AlexDeanDirector on closing night of @Tribeca Film Festival. 🌟🤩🌟 It was chosen as a selection last year but we couldn’t have the screening because of Covid. I’m so excited to see it again on a big screen. 🥰😍 Thank you to the millions of people who’ve watched my documentary on @YouTube and for all the letters and messages I’ve received about how it inspired you or you felt a connection to my story. ✨💓✨ Being honest and opening up about my trauma and my past wasn’t easy, but it was the best decision I ever made. 🥰 I know Teen Paris would be so proud of the woman I am today.👱🏻‍♀️ #TribecaFilmFestival 🎞 #Proud 💖 #ThisIsParis 🎥

node.text: Happy 17 Month Anniversary to my love Carter 💓💖💕 I’m so happy that our souls found each other in this life. 🥰 You lift me up and inspire me in ways you’ll never fully know and I’m so thankful 🥺💖💓 When I look back at the memories we’ve already created together, I get so emotional and excited thinking about the adventures that still await us and the experiences we are destined to enjoy in this life. You make me dream bigger than I ever have before. My twin flame 🔥🔥 My other half. I love our love!😍 #HappyAnniversary

node.text: In honor of my Grandma, I’m so grateful to have included her memory in my first #NFT exhibition with the piece “Hummingbird In My Metaverse.” 💕🕊💕 Today is her birthday, I miss her so much.🥺 She was such a force in my life. Thank you @BlakeKathryn for helping me bring this piece to life. Before my grandma passed away, she told me that she’d always be with me as a hummingbird. 💫✨🕊✨💫 Each time I go to Palm Springs where I used to live with her, a hummingbird always follows me around and it’s the best reminder that she’s always watching over me. 🥰🕊 She was such a strong and powerful woman and I know she’d be so so proud of the woman I’ve become today. 💕💕 Happy Birthday, love and miss you forever Grandma💖

node.text: Back in 2017 for my @Netflix film #TheAmericanMeme, I envisioned a virtual world where people could DJ and hang out and be their own avatars. 💫👾👥 It’s amazing how with the #NFT movement these virtual worlds actually exist now, with people existing virtually in the metaverse. 🌐💥 I’ve always been ahead of my time and obsessed with new technology. It’s so cool to see my prediction come true! 💓💖 #Pioneer #Trailblazer #LovesIt

node.text: Can someone please help me find an extension cord? 😹❤️ I’m loving all of your reactions and sweet messages so far on my new @Netflix show, #CookingWithParis. Tag #CookingWithParis and I’ll be reposting my faves. 🥰💕🥰 #ChefParis 👩🏼‍🍳✨🔥
